8. Offering credit rating services;
9. Operating a recognised stock exchange;
10. Acting as a depository for securities;
11. Acting as a registrar to an issuer of securities;
12. Providing underwriting services for securities, commodity products, or derivatives;
13. Offering portfolio management services;
14. Acting as a financial advisor or consultant;
15. Providing investment banking services;
16. Operating a clearing corporation;
17. Acting as a custodian bank for securities, commodity products, or derivatives;
18. Offering trading-related services in securities, commodity products, or derivatives;
19. Providing financial data and analytics services;
20. Operating a recognised clearing corporation;
21. Acting as a recognised clearing corporation;
22. Acting as a recognised depository;
23. Acting as a recognised investment exchange;
24. Offering any other service not specified in the regulations.

These restrictions are intended to ensure that TechFin and Ancillary Service Providers do not engage in activities that could compromise financial stability or create conflicts of interest.
